CSS notes

In-line notes: place css code inside html sections
<h1 style="color:red;">Prework Study Guide</h1>

Internal Style Sheet: include css code in seperate <style> category in head
    <head>
    <style>
      h1 {
        color: red;
      }
    </style>
   </head>

External CSS Style Sheet: create <link> to external page inside head
    <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./assests/style.css" />
    </head>
    rel indicates the relationship between the linked information and the html page
    href indicates the location of the information

Command Line: cd assets, then touch "style.css"

Examples:
    <div {color: blue; text-align:justify;}
    * = selector applying to all elements on page
    use a comma to apply two selectors to a css rule {}
    header,
    footer {
        width: 100%;
        height: 120px;
        background-color: blue;
        color: white;
    }

Class elements allow CSS to apply only to specified elements within the html code